   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Papers of the Continental Congress. Originals in the National Archives: Record Group 360. Microfilm edition in 204 reels. Usually cited in the present work from the microfilms, but according to the original series and volume numbering devised in the State Department in the early 19th century; for example, PCC, No. 93, III, i.e. the third volume of series 93.&lt;/expan&gt; ]">PCC</span>, No. 84, IV, f. 297299); internal address: M<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">r</span> Secretary Livingston. <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ letterbook copy (Letterbook copies are normally unsigned, but any such copy is assumed to be in the hand of the person responsible for the text unless it is otherwise described.) ]">LbC</abbr> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>); <span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Formerly, Adams Papers, Microfilms. The corpus of the Adams Papers, 16391889, as published on microfilm by the Massachusetts Historical Society, 19541959, in 608 reels. Cited in the present work, when necessary, by reel number. Available in research libraries throughout the United States and in a few libraries in Canada, Europe, and New Zealand.&lt;/expan&gt; ]">APM</span> Reel 108.</p>
</div>
        <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0041-fn-0001-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0041-fn-0001">1</a>
   <p>With the exception of the third paragraph, this letter is a summary, with some phrasing included verbatim, of <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s very long Diary entry for 20 Nov., which is devoted to accounts of that days conversations with Benjamin Franklin and John Jay (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Diary and Autobiography of John Adams&lt;/i&gt;, ed. L. H. Butterfield and others, Cambridge, 1961; 4 vols. ]">JA, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">D&amp;A</span></span>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-01-03-02-0001-0004-0014%20ADMS-print-01-03-02-0001-0004-0015#ADMS-01-03-02-pb-0063" class="pageNo">3:6368</a>).</p>
</div>
        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0041-fn-0002-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0041-fn-0002">2</a>
   <p>The arguments that Benjamin Vaughan was taking to London to use in discussions with Lord Shelburne likely were derived, at least in <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s mind, from a conversation between <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> and Vaughan on 16 Nov. that centered on what should or should not be done regarding the loyalists in the peace treaty (same, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-01-03-02-0001-0004-0012#ADMS-01-03-02-pb-0057" class="pageNo">3:5758</a>).</p>
</div>
        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0041-fn-0003-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0041-fn-0003">3</a>
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s confidence about the tenor of Richard Oswalds letters likely is owing to conversations that <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> had with Oswald on 15 and 18 Nov. concerning the loyalists and the future of Anglo-American and Franco-American relations (same, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-01-03-02-0001-0004-0009%20ADMS-print-01-03-02-0001-0004-0010%20ADMS-print-01-03-02-0001-0004-0011%20ADMS-print-01-03-02-0001-0004-0012#ADMS-01-03-02-pb-0054" class="pageNo">3:5457</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-01-03-02-0001-0004-0012%20ADMS-print-01-03-02-0001-0004-0013#ADMS-01-03-02-pb-0059" class="pageNo">5961</a>).</p>
</div>
